已过时的 API

目录

  • 已过时的方法
  • 已过时的方法 
    方法和说明
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.StringUtils.chomp(String, String)
    This feature will be removed in Lang 4.0, use StringUtils.removeEnd(String, String) instead
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ObjectUtils.equals(Object, Object)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.equals(Object, Object) in Java 7 and will be removed from future releases.
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ObjectUtils.hashCode(Object)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.hashCode(Object) in Java 7 and will be removed in future releases
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ObjectUtils.hashCodeMulti(Object...)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.hash(Object...) in Java 7 and will be removed in future releases.
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ArrayUtils.isEquals(Object, Object)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.deepEquals(Object, Object) and will be removed from future releases.
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.StringUtils.toString(byte[], String)
    use StringUtils.toEncodedString(byte[], Charset) instead of String constants in your code
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ObjectUtils.toString(Object)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.toString(Object) in Java 7 and will be removed in future releases. Note however that said method will return "null" for null references, while this method returns and empty String. To preserve behavior use java.util.Objects.toString(myObject, "")
    org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.ObjectUtils.toString(Object, String)
    this method has been replaced by java.util.Objects.toString(Object, String) in Java 7 and will be removed in future releases.
